main event: Four dull silver circular objects were observed in the sky over Bangor, Maine on 4 August 1965.
interesting points: The sighting lasted for about 20 seconds,The objects moved from north to south and then three turned east while one continued south,Witnesses were looking at lighting effects on the sky from the state fair grounds during the observation,Local radar stations reported no contacts in the area at the time of the sighting,The official conclusion was that the sighting was possibly a reflection from jet exhaust haze or lights from amusement rides at the state fair.
witness description: railroad enginemen from Bangor and Frankfort, Maine
